>> time required: 25 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/recipe-image-legacy-id-192471_11-88af07f.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat the @oil{1%tbsp} in a large saucepan, then fry the @onion{1} and @celery{2} gently for ~{10%min}s until softened, stirring frequently. Tip in the @cumin{2%tsp} and fry for another min.

Turn up the heat, then add the @stock{600%ml}, @tomatoes{400%g} and @chickpeas{400%g}, plus a good grind of black pepper. Simmer for ~{8%min}s. Throw in @broad beans{100%g} and @lemon{0.5} juice, cook for a further ~{2%min}s. Season to taste, then top with a sprinkling of lemon zest and chopped herbs. Serve with @flatbread{0%large}.
